https://www.englisch-hilfen.de/en/exercises/pronouns/mix.htm
[…] lives in Liverpool. (he)
I met […] in the office. (he)
They sing with […] in the choir. (I)
Lisa likes […]. (it)
Excuse […], is this the way to the station? (I)
[…] worked in the garden. (we)
Where are the cupcakes? Did you eat […]? (they)
Is […] your sister? (she)
Where are […] from? (you)
[…] saw Jack in the office. (we)
He lives in Liverpool.
I met him in the office.
They sing with me in the choir.
Lisa likes it.
Excuse me, is this the way to the station?
We worked in the garden.
Where are the cupcakes? Did you eat them?
Is she your sister?
Where are you from?
We saw Jack in the office.

https://www.englisch-hilfen.de/en/exercises/pronouns/personal_pronouns5.htm
To można przerobić na zadanie z pytaniem o prawidłowy zaimek.
I am from Berlin. →
Can Mr Henderson help me? →
We live in London. →
This book is for her. →
He is not at school. →
This present is for us. →
This is a new house. It is blue. →
Where are you from? →
Don't ask them! →
The children can see you. →
I am from Berlin. → subject form
Can Mr Henderson help me? → object form
We live in London. → subject form
This book is for her. → object form
He is not at school. → subject form
This present is for us. → object form
This is a new house. It is blue. → subject form
Where are you from? → subject form
Don't ask them! → object form
The children can see you. → object form

